Preheat oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Place rice in a small saucepan. Cover with water and stir in salt. Cook over low heat until water is absorbed, about 20 minutes. In a large bowl, beat eggs. Beat in milk, sugar and vanilla. Stir in rice. Pour into a 2 quart baking dish. Dot with butter. Bake in preheated oven 45 minutes, until set.